House Bill 906
By: Representative Smith of the 41st
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 8 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to the Long-term Care Ombudsman Program, so as to require long-term care
3 facilities to post a link on their websites to the official website of the office of the long-term
4 care ombudsman; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 3 of Chapter 8 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
9 Long-term Care Ombudsman Program, is amended by revising Code Section 31-8-59,
10 relating to notice to residents, as follows:
11 "31-8-59.
12 (a) The state ombudsman shall prepare and distribute to each long-term care facility in the
13 state a written notice describing the long-term care ombudsman program and the procedure
14 to follow in making a complaint, including the address and telephone number of the state
15 ombudsman and community ombudsman, if any. The administrator shall give the written
16 notice required by this Code section subsection to each resident and his or her legally
