17 appointed guardian, if any, upon admission. The administrator shall also post such written
18 notice in conspicuous public places in the facility in accordance with procedures provided
19 by the state ombudsman and shall give such notice to any resident and his or her legally
20 appointed guardian, if any, who did not receive it upon admission. The failure to provide
21 the notices required by this Code section subsection shall be a ground upon which the
22 department may revoke any permit issued to a long-term care facility under Code Section
23 31-7-1 Article 1 of this chapter.
24 (b) Each individual long-term care facility which maintains a website shall post in a
25 prominent location on such website a link to the official website of the office of the state
26 long-term care ombudsman."
27 SECTION 2.
28 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
